 Resumo
 Full-time on Wearside, and Liverpool prevail in some
 grizzly conditions to beat Sunderland 1-0 at the Stadium of
 Light.  Arne Slot's travelling men have Virgil van Dijk to
 thank, with his goal a stoic difference-maker in a tight
 and well-contested battle. Following some decent
 half-chances in the first period, like Florian Wirtz most
 notably hitting the right post through a crowded box, this
 goal just past the hour was the culmination of continued
 set-piece pressure. Sunderland's defensive heroics put the
 likes of Reinildo and Dan Ballard in the spotlight. Yet,
 the dirty work's charm ran out, and Mohamed Salah curled in
 a peach of a corner for Van Dijk to glance in, with a
 scrambling Habib Diarra on the line unable to clear.
 Although this wasn't exactly a game for the ages, Salah's
 set-piece puts him on par with Steven Gerrard's 92 Premier
 League assists. It also helps Liverpool keep on the
 Champions League trail in sixth as they sit three points
 off Manchester United in fourth, even if they did play
 below their 1.95 xG. After this outing, where they
 underperformed their 0.66 xG, Sunderland stay in 11th,
 still reserving the chance to break into the top eight.
 Thank you for joining us tonight. We hope you enjoyed the
 game!

