 Resumo
 The spoils are shared following an exciting climax at the
 Gtech Community Stadium, where Premier League leaders
 Arsenal have been held to a 1-1 draw by a spirited
 Brentford. The Gunners registered an xG of just 0.6,
 representing their general lack of a cutting edge, as they
 miss the chance to restore their six-point lead at the
 summit. Following a disappointing first half, Arteta's side
 increased their urgency after the break and took the lead
 in the 61st minute, when Madueke headed in from Hincapie's
 cross. Arsenal had the chance to double their lead soon
 after, but Gyokeres had the ball stolen off his toes by
 Kayode when it looked like he would slot in from close
 range. That intervention proved crucial as Brentford, who
 had an xG of 1.34, equalised on 71 minutes, with Van den
 Berg flicking on Kayode's long throw for Lewis-Potter to
 head home. Both sides went close to winning the match.
 Mosquera superbly blocked Thiago, who was one-on-one with
 Raya, while Martinelli was denied by Kelleher at the other
 end. After earning a point apiece, the two teams are in FA
 Cup action this weekend. Arsenal host Wigan Athletic on
 Sunday, with Brentford travelling to Macclesfield the
 following day. That's all for today. Thanks for joining us.
 Until next time, goodbye!

