 Resumo
 The full-time whistle blows at Villa Park as Aston Villa
 secure a narrow 1-0 victory over Brighton to keep their
 Premier League title hopes alive! After a cagey first half
 that saw little in the way of goalmouth action - aside from
 a wide long-range drive from Buendia and a very tame effort
 inside the box from Welbeck at the other end - both sides
 emerged from the break with more energy. Kadioglu struck
 the woodwork with a fierce effort that Martinez just barely
 parried 10 minutes into the second half, while Mitoma,
 Konsa, and Rogers all fashioned half-chances that went
 begging. Villa finally broke the deadlock in the 86th
 minute as Mings’ header struck Hinshelwood on its way into
 the net, earning the hosts a vital three points that sees
 them, at least temporarily, move within six points of
 Premier League leaders Arsenal. Brighton, meanwhile, remain
 in 14th, seven points adrift of the drop zone after
 extending their winless run to six matches. Neither side
 created chances in great volume or quality, with Villa
 managing 0.67 xG to Brighton’s 0.46. That’s all from us
 tonight, thank you for joining this live commentary. We
 hope you’ve enjoyed it!

